subject: College Athletics
lead_paragraph: Tyrell Gatewood, a senior safety at Texas, was released from jail after his arrest on drug charges, the fifth arrest of a Longhorns player since June. Gatewood, 22, was charged with two counts of possession of a dangerous drug.
